    <title type="html"><![CDATA[some lessons on altering mysql storage engine]]></title>
    <link href="http://ukanga.github.io/blog/2013/05/20/some-lessons-on-altering-mysql-storage-engine/"/>
    <updated>2013-05-20T11:46:00+03:00</updated>
    <id>http://ukanga.github.io/blog/2013/05/20/some-lessons-on-altering-mysql-storage-engine</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Check what storage engine a particular table is using:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='mysql'><span class='line'><span class="k">SELECT</span> <span class="n">table_name</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="kp">engine</span> <span class="k">FROM</span> <span class="n">INFORMATION_SCHEMA</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="kp">TABLES</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Changing storage engine of a table;</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='mysql'><span class='line'><span class="k">ALTER</span> <span class="k">TABLE</span> <span class="ss">`table_name1`</span> <span class="kp">ENGINE</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">MyISAM</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>When altering a table engine from InnoDB to MyISAM, you have to delete all constraints
 on the table otherwise you will get a foreign key constraint error. You can check the
 constraints within a form using</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='mysql'><span class='line'><span class="k">SHOW</span> <span class="k">CREATE</span> <span class="k">TABLE</span> <span class="ss">`table_name1`</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>You can then drop the constraints like:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='mysql'><span class='line'><span class="k">ALTER</span> <span class="k">TABLE</span> <span class="ss">`table_mame1`</span> <span class="k">DROP</span> <span class="k">FOREIGN</span> <span class="k">KEY</span> <span class="ss">`user_id_refs_id_1e020b58278eec2b`</span><span class="p">;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>`</p>
]]></content>
